# Enhancements Backlog

## ENH-001 — Multi-experiment folder structure

**Status:** Proposed

Restructure the project to support multiple named experiments, each fully self-contained and reproducible.

### Folder layout

```
psych_llm_study/
├── experiments/
│   └── <experiment-id>/
│       ├── experiment.json      # experiment definition (see schema below)
│       ├── exp_questions.json   # frozen copy of questions used in this run
│       ├── exp_models.json      # frozen subset of models used in this run
│       └── results/
│           └── run_TIMESTAMP.db
├── models.json                  # global model registry (unchanged)
├── questions.json               # global question bank (unchanged, used as source)
├── scripts/
│   ├── run_study.py             # gains --experiment <id>
│   └── analyze_results.py       # gains --experiment <id>
├── tests/
└── logs/
```

### experiment.json schema

```json
{
  "experiment_id": "moral-reasoning-pilot",
  "name": "Moral Reasoning Pilot Study",
  "description": "...",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-05-09",
  "author": "toddfirsich",
  "questions_file": "exp_questions.json",
  "models_file": "exp_models.json",
  "run_config": {
    "timeout": 240,
    "temperature": 0.7
  }
}
```

### Key decisions

- `exp_questions.json` and `exp_models.json` are frozen copies made at experiment creation time — editing the globals afterward does not affect a completed experiment
- `exp_models.json` is a subset of the global `models.json` (same schema, fewer entries)
- `models.json` remains the single source of truth for backend/capability metadata
- `run_study.py` resolves all paths relative to the experiment folder
- Results go into `experiments/<id>/results/` not the top-level `results/`

### Scripts changes required

- `run_study.py` — add `--experiment <id>` flag; load paths from `experiment.json`
- `analyze_results.py` — add `--experiment <id>` flag; scope queries to that experiment's results folder
- New helper (optional): `scripts/new_experiment.py` — scaffolds a new experiment folder, copies and filters globals into `exp_*` files

